      "why": "**Why two variables instead of an array?** The recurrence only ever looks back one and two\nsteps, so storing the whole `dp` array is wasteful. Collapsing it to `prev1`/`prev2` keeps\nthe O(n) time but drops memory to O(1) — the classic \"rolling DP\" space optimization.",
